HEADWORD: cha-cha
<hw>cha-cha</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a modern ballroom dance from Latin
America; it uses two slow steps followed by three quick small steps,
with swaying movements of the hips, and has many variations of movements
based on that rhythm.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cha-cha.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

